body:
Officially, iCEcube2 only supports a limited set of SB_MAC16 configurations, documented in the relevant sections of the iCE40 technology library. For example, setting A_REG but not B_REG isn't allowed. 

The reason for this, afaik, is that iCEcube2 only provides timing data for a limited set of modes, and it is also theoretically possible but unlikely that some of the "unsupported" modes have silicon issues.

As it stands, icestorm only ever built timing documentation for the supported modes as they were all that iCEcube2 had. We could extrapolate the other modes in nextpnr (it should mostly just be a case of mixing and matching delays from two modes); but perhaps it is better if Yosys stuck to supported configurations in the first place.

Not sure what the best approach is to things like this. 

Example:

```verilog
module top(input clk, input [15:0] a, b, output [31:0] q);

reg [15:0] aa;

always @(posedge clk)
	aa <= a;

assign q = aa * b;

endmodule
```

